> **This file is the project constitution.** Every rule below is a hard constraint â€” not a suggestion, not a guideline. Copilot must follow these rules in all interactions with this repository without exception. When in doubt, these instructions take precedence over general knowledge or external best practices.

# Architecture

Next.js 16 App Router application â€” a GitHub Copilot usage analytics dashboard with PostgreSQL backend. Standalone output mode for Docker deployment. No monorepo â€” single application.

Route group `(app)` wraps all authenticated pages with config + session checks.

```
src/
  app/           â†’ Next.js App Router pages and API routes
    (app)/       â†’ Route group for authenticated pages (layout checks config + session)
    api/         â†’ REST API routes
  components/    â†’ UI components organized by domain folder (usage/, dashboard/, teams/, shared/)
  entities/      â†’ TypeORM EntitySchema definitions + TypeScript interfaces
  lib/           â†’ Shared business logic and helpers
    hooks/       â†’ Client-side React hooks
    validations/ â†’ Zod schemas for request validation
    __tests__/   â†’ Unit tests for lib modules
  test/          â†’ Test infrastructure (setup, db-helpers)
migrations/      â†’ TypeORM migration files (timestamped)
e2e/             â†’ Playwright E2E tests
  helpers/       â†’ E2E helper utilities (auth, db)
specifications/  â†’ Feature specs, task plans, story plans
```

